SIMPLE: spiculate
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spiculate
<hw>Spic"u*late</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>spiculatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>spiculare</ets> to sharpen, to
point, fr. <ets>spiculum</ets> a dart.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Covered
with, or having, spicules.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Covered with minute spiculae, or
pointed fleshy appendages; divided into small spikelets.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spiculate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Spiculate
<hw>Spic"u*late</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To sharpen to a
point.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧With <xex>spiculated</xex>
paling.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Mason.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spicule</ent>⟦br⟧
